stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: Malicious advertising campaign associated with the Neutrino exploit kit
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
On July 25, 2013, several domains were identified in a malicious advertising campaign that used the Neutrino Exploit Kit. Malicious files associated with the exploit kit were hosted on the following sites:
ad.yieldmanager.com xce4h.info fifxqgymlgshju.is-a-geek.org kdkynmcytliluwdyot.is-a-geek.org kmoixdwtguuuitoisb.is-a-geek.org kpqeqregusestrpmwm.is-a-geek.org http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.1/jquery.min.js
In March 2013, the Neutrino Exploit Kit was known to exploit vulnerabilities listed in CVE-2013-0431 and CVE-2012-1723.
References regarding Neutrino Exploit Kit: http://malforsec.blogspot.com/2013/07/yet-another-encounter-with-neutrino-ek.html http://blog.trendmicro.com/trendlabs-security-intelligence/a-new-exploit-kit-in-neutrino/

stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
The attacker inserted malicious advertisements in the ad.yieldmanager.com network to redirect some advertisements to this URL: http://xce4h.info/search.php?username=index&query=Men's Clothing
The URL http://xce4h.info/search.php?username=index&query=Men's Clothing refers to http://fifxqgymlgshju.is-a-geek.org:8000/sjuke?dtmcdmwl=2591216 and other multiple subdomains of is-a-geek.org:
Yield Manager is a legitimate advertising technology system owned by Yahoo. It uses tracking cookies saved on the user's system. It is known to submit the user's browser data such as names, contact information, and online forms. Yield Manager had been previously compromised in other malicious advertisement campaigns associated with spyware or other malicious activity.
References for ad.yieldmanager: http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2012/apr/24/yieldmanager-tracking-trackers-cookies-web-monitoring http://www.ehow.com/how_5104180_remove-adyieldmanager.html http://botcrawl.com/how-to-remove-the-ad-yieldmanager-virus/
